7. Mathematical Core Summary (For Interviews)

Framework Mathematics Physical Insight
Homogenization Two‑scale asymptotic expansion,  \mathbf{u} = \mathbf{u}_0(\mathbf{x}) + \epsilon \mathbf{u}_1(\mathbf{x},\mathbf{y})  Grain‑scale contacts → bulk wave properties
Contact Mechanics Hertz–Mindlin–JKR:  k_n \propto (F_n R^*)^{1/3}  Stiffness increases with confining pressure and sintering
Langevin Dynamics  m\ddot{\mathbf{x}} = \mathbf{F} - \gamma \dot{\mathbf{x}} + \boldsymbol{\xi}(t)  Stochastic grain motion with granular temperature
First‑Passage Time  \langle \tau \rangle = \int_0^\infty \exp(-\Delta U / k_B T_{gr}) dt  Probabilistic fluidization criterion
Fokker‑Planck  \partial_t W = -\nabla \cdot (\mathbf{F}_{\text{rad}} W/\gamma) + \nabla \cdot (D\nabla W)  Probability density of ice particle position
Persistent Homology Betti numbers \beta_0, \beta_1, \beta_2, persistence diagrams Quantifies force chain topology
Variational PINNs Minimize action  S = \int (T - V) dt  + PDE residuals Thermodynamically consistent ML

