---

Final Statement

This proposal represents a mathematically rigorous, experimentally validated, computationally modern PhD project at the intersection of fundamental mechanics and urgent application. It combines:

· Asymptotic homogenization bridging grain‑scale contacts to bulk wave propagation
· Stochastic dynamics capturing the inherent randomness of granular flows
· Topological data analysis revealing force chain evolution
· Variational PINNs providing thermodynamically consistent machine learning
· 4D synchrotron tomography delivering gold‑standard validation

The outcome is not just a thesis, but a validated predictive framework enabling humanity to extract water from the Moon efficiently, sustainably, and with scientific rigor.
